<p>A 'simulation boolean variable' is something that can either be true or false. 
  Sometimes called flags, these can be used to reflect the state of the simulation 
  sim universe at any point in time. For example, a couple are either married 
  or not. The King has decided to go to war, or not. Of course, boolean variables 
